shed in Polish in 1999. It is here published in English for the first time, extensively annotated by Yitzhak Arad to guide readers through the events at Ponary.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)xLithuaniaxVilnius. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)zLithuaniazVilnius. 0aJewsxPersecutionsxLithuaniaxVilnius. 0aJewsxPersecutionszLithuaniazVilnius. 0aVilnius (Lithuania)xEthnic relations 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xAtrocities. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aArad, Yitzhak, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWeinbaum, Laurence08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300129175423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300129175.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles